    28  // Interface can be implemented by anything that knows how to watch and report changes.
    29  type Interface interface {
    30          // Stop tells the producer that the consumer is done watching, so the
    31          // producer should stop sending events and close the result channel. The
    32          // consumer should keep watching for events until the result channel is
    33          // closed.
    34          //
    35          // Because some implementations may create channels when constructed, Stop
    36          // must always be called, even if the consumer has not yet called
    37          // ResultChan().
    38          //
    39          // Only the consumer should call Stop(), not the producer. If the producer
    40          // errors and needs to stop the watch prematurely, it should instead send
    41          // an error event and close the result channel.
    42          Stop()
